I'll find him.
Stay put

166
00:23:38,076 --> 00:23:45,073
No sir, please! This apartment,
this car, servants...

167
00:23:45,283 --> 00:23:51,745
this sudden payhike, for no reason,
oh please don't be so kind to me

168
00:23:55,994 --> 00:24:00,954
I promise, I'll make Preeti
very happy, I'll pamper her

169
00:24:01,266 --> 00:24:08,001
But I want to be a self-made man.
I don't want to compromise my ideals

170
00:24:10,175 --> 00:24:18,549
Look Rajesh, had Preety married into
a big family, I would've liked them...

171
00:24:18,784 --> 00:24:30,889
to care for her like a daughter. Not
as a son-in-law, more like a son...

172
00:24:32,164 --> 00:24:34,724
can you not live in our house?
Like a member of our family?

173
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:37,925
Come, share our joys, our sorrows

174
00:24:50,749 --> 00:24:52,944
Why is God sending so much happiness
an orphan's way?

175
00:24:54,853 --> 00:24:56,912
Parents, brothers, sisters,
relationships...

176
00:24:57,155 --> 00:25:02,957
for me, they were mere words.
Meanings, I never even knew

177
00:25:03,295 --> 00:25:10,792
All this for me, in this very
lifetime? I can't believe this!

178
00:25:18,643 --> 00:25:21,339
Couldn't be a better man for Preeti,
not in this world

179
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:27,441
And you, Mummy-Papa's choice,
Preeti's paramour...

180
00:25:27,686 --> 00:25:28,914
are my friend

181
00:25:31,456 --> 00:25:32,548
Welcome...

182
00:25:32,757 --> 00:25:34,281
oh hello...

183
00:25:34,459 --> 00:25:35,585
hi lady... welcome

184
00:25:35,727 --> 00:25:38,696
Welcome... welcome...

185
00:25:38,930 --> 00:25:42,832
this smile is giving me a jaw-ache.
This was one offer I couldn't refuse

186
00:25:50,709 --> 00:25:55,476
How about a kiss?
Don't make me pine

187
00:25:55,714 --> 00:25:57,409
What...?
- You're my heartthrob

188
00:25:57,716 --> 00:26:03,245
My heart goes out to you.
- You lazy laggard

189
00:26:03,455 --> 00:26:07,915
Roadside Romeo! Savage!
Beast! Blackheart

190
00:26:08,293 --> 00:26:14,129
O'heartless one, your every torment
I shall bear. But I swear by you...

191
00:26:14,332 --> 00:26:18,462
you I have given my heart to!
- Uneducated loafer!

192
00:26:18,737 --> 00:26:24,369
You're insane! While you wait,
someone will whisk me away

193
00:26:24,543 --> 00:26:25,510
No!

194
00:26:25,710 --> 00:26:26,972
This no filmi plot

195
00:26:27,379 --> 00:26:29,347
And I'm not insane

196
00:26:29,581 --> 00:26:31,708
This is no love triangle

197
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:40,617
Just a simple straight love story.
A tale of twosomes...

198
00:26:40,792 --> 00:26:46,321
like Romeo and Juliet,
Laddoo and Sweety

199
00:26:46,932 --> 00:26:51,028
Moron! The legendary lovers
never married in the end

200
00:26:51,303 --> 00:26:55,000
The committed suicide, or they were
killed. Spare me, I don't want to die

201
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,730
Something is stirring in my heart.
- And then...?

202
00:26:56,875 --> 00:26:58,308
I'm in love
- And then...?

203
00:26:58,543 --> 00:27:00,067
Love is never defeated.
- And then...?

204
00:27:00,245 --> 00:27:01,644
I'm no less a man!
- And then...?

205
00:27:01,813 --> 00:27:03,974
I'm your prince charming!
- And then...?

206
00:27:04,215 --> 00:27:06,649
The lover will carry his bride away!
- And then...?

207
00:27:06,885 --> 00:27:08,785
Still stuck at "then"...?

208
00:27:08,987 --> 00:27:10,887
All superhits films, no?
- So...?

209
00:27:11,156 --> 00:27:16,389
Coming for a long drive?
- First get me a drink

210
00:27:16,661 --> 00:27:23,123
For attending my daughter's wedding,
for receiving my guests...

211
00:27:23,401 --> 00:27:32,901
I don't want to thank you. Because
your debts I can never pay off...

212
00:27:33,178 --> 00:27:39,014
with thanks.
- Sir, why embarrass us?

213
00:27:39,351 --> 00:27:43,117
Can we ever forget your debt?
- What a thing to say

214
00:27:43,455 --> 00:27:50,623
At weddings, we fathers have only
given our daughters away

215
00:27:50,929 --> 00:27:55,332
The rest of it, you have
always shouldered

216
00:27:55,634 --> 00:28:00,435
The one who is getting married today
is our daughter. Let us do our bit

217
00:28:00,705 --> 00:28:02,969
I'm thankful.
- Farewell

218
00:28:28,199 --> 00:28:32,295
Best wishes.
- Thanks a lot

219
00:28:32,537 --> 00:28:33,731
I've just concluded
a major responsibility

220
00:28:33,905 --> 00:28:36,203
But you still have
your responsibilities

221
00:28:39,611 --> 00:28:47,245
You have always had my best wishes.
One word of friendly advice

222
00:28:47,452 --> 00:28:52,685
Tell me.
- This is a grand wedding

223
00:28:52,991 --> 00:28:57,758
But you know the business community,
more enemies, than friends

224
00:28:58,430 --> 00:29:03,390
Your competition might be enthused.
- At chess, they can't checkmate me

225
00:29:03,768 --> 00:29:11,197
Can they checkmate me in business?

226
00:29:46,211 --> 00:29:48,509
You...!
- You...?

227
00:29:48,747 --> 00:29:51,511
What are you doing here?
- That's what I want to know

228
00:29:51,716 --> 00:29:58,212
It's my best friend's sister's wedding.
- Both, my sisters

229
00:29:58,656 --> 00:30:03,491
A savage? In such a good family?
- Such God willed

230
00:30:03,828 --> 00:30:10,461
Talking about savages, ever taken
a look at yourself? At your flaws?

231
00:30:10,735 --> 00:30:12,396
None that I see

232
00:30:12,570 --> 00:30:19,999
First, you're stubborn.
Second, you have a temper

233
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:29,418
Third, you're brainless. Fourth,
you love to flaunt your Dad's money

